		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=12030'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC6600;font-weight:bold; '>Tanares</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Master<br>
			
				Posts: 315<br>
				
				Registered: 03-24-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=12030'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/wood_elfl.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=10373#M10373">1</a> of 95
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 156 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV>Augments! Fletchable, tailorable, smithable (likely to have the most), bakable, brewable, JCable, pottery-made, TRADEABLE augments! But wait, you ask, what of the augments I bought with my hard earned points? Easy! Make the tradeskill augments maybe slightly under par to merchant boons... and make some of THOSE tradeable as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I for one would love to see augments made via tradeskills that could add melee skill mods (Say a +5% archery or +10% backstab mod) or focus effects (a cheapcost easily made set of Level 1 foci, etc.). Variety too! Fletching could be the skill that adds the Archery augment, research for spell casting foci, tinkering could give a flameless lantern light source, baking could yeild a focus that reduces food consumption... the possibilities would be endless! As for the EverQuest economy: believe me there will be a market for these items.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do you, my fellow players, think of this idea? As a tradeskill addict and avid adventurer I'd love to see player made augments (and heck let's throw some player made charms too, they are SO under-utilized)... would be a great way to further customize my gear!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Tanares the Wind Caller<br>Serving Luclin's dementia for 65 levels!
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
