		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>My suggestion is to allow people to make tradeskill items that are comparable to items you get from boss kills.&nbsp; It'll give people a way of obtaining items if they aren't in a big, established guild.&nbsp; I also think it's rediculous how much people have to pay for items that farmers daily camp.&nbsp; You have farmers that perma camp certain spots to always get items so that others have little chance at obtaining them.&nbsp; Then you go to the bazaar and pay those farmers high price on things they were perma camping.&nbsp; Believe it or not, there are many many people who aren't into the high end, uber guild things.&nbsp; And sometimes for them to advance is really bazaar shop or do their own tradeskills.</P>
<P>I used to put a lot of effort into tradeskills, got all tradeskills to 250 with no guild help, just me and my g/f working daily for 2-3 years.&nbsp; Then we joined a guild once, and found out how easy it was to just sit at a raid and not do much, and get items that are easily 3x better than tradeskill items that we have to farm, combine a hundred times, and chance at failing 50/50.&nbsp; If you want to satisfy the people who are getting frustrated with the game and have no intentions on doing the uber guild thing, I would suggest get the economy and market moving by providing better crafting items to tradeskillers.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
