Windtaurus wrote:<BR>
<DIV>While a developer is reading this board I would like to suggest overhaste coffee.&nbsp; In order to get the overhaste you have to actually consume the coffee not just keep it in a slot.&nbsp; And how bout EATEN stat food.&nbsp; Maybe habeneros if consumed gives you a sow type buff.&nbsp; Or something creative.&nbsp; Supper muffins slow you down but give massive damage boost.&nbsp; Just make it consumed not equiped and make the drops easy/inexpensive enought for it to be feesable.&nbsp; Can probably find something kewl for all tradeskills.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Oh yeah if&nbsp;a rogue fails at applying poison he poisones himself.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>This type of thinking was bounced around over and over when baked and brewed stat foods and drinks emmerged,&nbsp;back when the items said they had stats, but never actually did anything for you.&nbsp; Anyway, at the time they announced that the game mechanics just couldn't cope with "eaten" no longer in inventory items having any effect.</P>
<P>To be blunt I'm amazed they worked out finding the food in your inventory and applying it to the right stats to begin with.&nbsp; </P>
